<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9994> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9994" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Liguribus Apuaneis. MRR I.388, Itgenshorst no. 188, Rich no. 187." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8473> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8473" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 731" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2450> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2450" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "His imperium prorogued in Liguria, he transferred the Apuani to Samnium, and celebrated a triumph (Liv. 40.36.7, 37.8-38.9; see Degrassi 554). Cf. Nissen, Ital. Landeskunde 2.814f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2408> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2408" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Nep. Hann. 13.1; Liv. 40.18.1, and 35.1; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 122, 456f.; Val. Max. 1.1.12; 2.5.1; Plin. NH 13.85, with Cass. Hem.{384} fr. 37 Peter; Plut. Num. 22.5; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod. Both Consuls were assigned to Liguria and Baebius returned to hold the elections (Liv. 40.18.3, 26.5-6, and 35.1). They instituted the first bribery law (Liv. 40.12.11; cf. FOR 1.54f., 187; Schol. Bob. 2.78 Stangl); and Baebius a law to require the election of 4 and 6 Praetors, respectively, on alternate years (Liv. 40.44.2; cf. FOR 1.54f., 187)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2359> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2359" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "They reported to the Senate at the beginning of 184 (Polyb. 22.11.1, and 12.5-10; Liv. 39.33.1)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2333> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2333" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent to deal with disputes between Philip of Macedon and his neighbors in Greece and with complaints arising from his occupation of Aenus and Maronea (Polyb. 22.6; 23.2.7; Liv. 39.23.5-29.3, cf. 33.1; Pausan. 7.8.6). They also discussed the Achaean treatment of Sparta with the Achaean magistrates, who refused Metellus' request that they call an assembly (Polyb. 22.10; 23.4.7; Diod. 29.17; Pausan. 7.8.6, and 9.1)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2330> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2330" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Livy reports this embassy under the year 185, but the appointment could have been made late in the consular year 186. I accept Niese's dating (3.22, note 1). They could leave Rome in the spring, visit Tempe and Thessalonica, and be at Argos for the Nemean games in August (Polyb. 22.10.1)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2178> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2178" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Was active as Propraetor (Liv. 36.8.6) in Macedonia and Greece during the winter and served with Glabrio (Liv. 36.10.10, 13.1-9, and 22.8; App. Syr. 16)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2151> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2151" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Prepared ships and legions for the crossing to Epirus (Liv. 35.20.12-13, 23.5, and 24.7; 36.1.7, 8.6, and 10.10; App. Syr. 16; Zon. 9.19)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2149> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2149" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elections: Liv. 35.10.11 Provinces and armies 35.20.8." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2111> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2111" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Colonized Sipontum (Liv. 34.45.3)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2099> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2099" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "CIL 1\n     .2.585, Lex. Agr. of 111, V. 43." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2098> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2098" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Mommsen identified the M. Baebius mentioned in the Lex Agraria of 111, who was both Tr. Pl. and IIIvir col. deduc., with the IIIvir of 194 (CIL 1\n   \n    1\n   \n   , p. 95). Niccolini holds that this, though possible, is uncertain, since the other references in this law are to laws and officials of recent date (FTP 418f.); furthermore, we do not know the names of the colonial commissioners appointed under the Gracchan program. See also Carcopino, Autour des Gracques 258ff." .
